Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:18.34,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0015,,{\blur3}I have a big gun, I took it from my Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.55,0:00:21.79,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Sick with Justice, I just wanna feel you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.02,0:00:25.20,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'm your angel, only a ring away...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.32,0:00:28.55,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You make me violate you, no matter who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.53,0:00:38.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's all up to you, no one lives forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Been burn in the hell, by all those pigs out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.34,0:00:45.53,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}It's always been hell, from when I was born...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:48.72,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}They make me violate them, no matter who they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:52.26,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fs79}Get down on your knees! Get a good head on your shoulders!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:55.69,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}If it's for your guys, go to the end of the Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.69,0:00:59.00,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Do what you think, give it with dedication...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:01:02.27,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}I'll put out your misery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.36,0:01:05.67,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}You made a mess! For Christ sakes, this rotten world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.67,0:01:09.10,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Shit out of luck! Go with my vision!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.10,0:01:12.54,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Light up the fire! Right on the power!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.54,0:01:15.90,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:24.48,Black Lagoon OP Credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Weapon... I have it all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.05,0:01:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm offering\N150 thousand?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.72,0:01:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't matter! Kill them...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.66,0:01:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then don't forget to pick up the cash\Non the ground when you're done!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.26,0:01:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. Do not move, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.53,0:01:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Negotiations... have been broken off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.64,0:01:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Damn you!\N- There they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.01,0:02:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jodorowsky here!\NEncountered enemy at Point Pskov!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.08,0:02:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.25,0:02:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.58,0:02:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Eda!\NIt's Hotel Moscow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.19,0:02:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've come out, big sister.\NIt's the Russians!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.59,0:02:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.86,0:02:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, big sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.39,0:02:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's confuse the Russians.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.93,0:02:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can randomly eliminate a few,\Nthey'll return to their main base for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.37,0:02:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.13,0:02:23.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's take separate routes\Nand corner the Russians!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.30,0:02:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I wish you success, big sister.\N- Yes, big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.57,0:02:31.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I love you.\N- Yes. I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.29,0:02:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We lost the targets during combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.89,0:02:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we've clearly shown ourselves\Nto the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.33,0:02:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instruct them to proceed and assume\Nthat the enemy has taken the bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.20,0:02:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All units,\Ncontinue with the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.90,0:02:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Lavochek Unit, Lobosfski Unit,{\i0}\N{\i1}complete level two preparations...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:02:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and proceed to the final location.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.48,0:03:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Target Two located behind{\i0}\N{\i1}Jodorowsky as he's retreating.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.78,0:03:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirm the number of targets.\NAt once!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.75,0:03:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Baronin to Okchabriagin.\NI have only sighted Target Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.62,0:03:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I repeat, {\i1}I have only sighted{\i0}\N{\i1}Target Two.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.69,0:03:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Private Eugene here. We have located\Nthe target that is following Jodorowsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.43,0:03:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only see one body\Nfrom here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.27,0:03:29.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Target Two is securely locked on{\i0}\N{\i1}to Jodorowsky's ass.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.00,0:03:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drag him along\Nto the planned location.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.14,0:03:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So only Target Two has taken the bait?\N- {\i1}That's correct.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine. Then make sure\Nto corner that one without mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:41.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't take anything for granted.{\i0}\N{\i1}They're extremely clever.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.41,0:03:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let them believe that they{\i0}\N{\i1}have the advantage.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.55,0:03:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With that in mind, proceed to{\i0}\N{\i1}the next stage and stir up confusion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have my subordinates take them\Non mafia-style.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.26,0:03:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to worry, we're almost at the\Npark entrance. We'll make the first shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.03,0:04:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Focus all your efforts on getting\Nthe target disturbed and furious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.17,0:04:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Frustration will dull the\Ntarget's senses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when\Nwe'll turn the tables.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.77,0:04:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Roger.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.58,0:04:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sergeant, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Take command of the final unit.\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Best of luck to you, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.52,0:04:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. And you be careful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.23,0:04:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.63,0:04:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess it's about time\Nwe put an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to this boisterous merrymaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.43,0:04:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you expect me to return\Nto the church empty handed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.70,0:04:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We should've agreed to that offer!\NYou got too greedy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.91,0:04:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think it was\Nthat saved you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...from getting your balls torn off by\Nthose guys from Hotel Moscow?! Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born without balls,\Nyou monkey-girl! Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking for it, you shit!\NWe'll have a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.39,0:04:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like fun, Revy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.83,0:05:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it will be more fun\Nafter you get more holes in your ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.40,0:05:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know...\NI really don't care anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.87,0:05:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't get a penny outta this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.74,0:05:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going back to the office.\NCall me if something comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.21,0:05:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait! What about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.18,0:05:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- What do you mean?\N- What do you think?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.52,0:05:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna walk into the\Nline of fire alone to go get my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.16,0:05:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me, Revy!\NWe're friends, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can go on your own.\NYou're not a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.33,0:05:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.43,0:05:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you be so cruel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.34,0:05:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.68,0:05:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long have you been there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.98,0:05:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting until you were alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.38,0:05:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't wanna face the two of you\Nall by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.79,0:06:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I want you\Nto help me with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.49,0:06:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as big brother kills\Nthe Russian lady, we'll have to flee.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.60,0:06:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we killed Verocchio and his men,\Nwho were supposed to arrange all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool. You knew all that,\Nand yet you killed your guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.47,0:06:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, now you no longer have\Nan obligation to kill Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.21,0:06:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why continue? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.18,0:06:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why, you ask? What a question.\NThat's so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.99,0:06:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we want to. There's no other\Nreason at all. We want to, so we do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.33,0:06:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not important right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.03,0:06:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to introduce me\Nto an escape specialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.50,0:06:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want someone who takes their job\Nseriously. Tell me, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.38,0:07:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to hide.\NCome out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.88,0:07:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could tell I was here.\NYou're amazing, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.62,0:07:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder your subordinates\Nare so skilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I chased them all over,\Nbut couldn't kill a single one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.26,0:07:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what do you suggest\Nwe do, lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.26,0:07:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we take advantage of\Nthis opportunity and talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.27,0:07:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps we can talk about\Nthat man we killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.94,0:08:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone else would've died\Na lot sooner...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.47,0:08:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but that man lasted\Nfor quite some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.11,0:08:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He kept yelling to the very end,\N"Captain! Captain!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.55,0:08:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over,\Nwhile spitting out blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.66,0:08:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.06,0:08:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a cold person, lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.03,0:08:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what?\NYou'll be like that man soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.43,0:08:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a shame that you don't\Nhave much time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.47,0:08:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That really is a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.74,0:08:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to say this, little boy,\Nbut this is the end of the road for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.88,0:08:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.54,0:08:43.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to apologize for your\Nmischievous pranks. Hey, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.85,0:08:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, kneel there before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.25,0:08:50.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- You're not serious.\N- Kneel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.08,0:09:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the end for you, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.65,0:09:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only you had the ability to use reason,\Nyou would've realized...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.25,0:09:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you walked straight into a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.49,0:09:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, you're gonna die here,\Nas nothing but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.93,0:09:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a brat beyond repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.50,0:09:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady, you're funny.\NWhat are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.14,0:09:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not die.\NI'm not gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.17,0:09:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I've killed so many people!\NWe've killed many, many...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.18,0:09:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...many, many...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.95,0:09:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...people. Therefore we can live on...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.28,0:09:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.72,0:09:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can... We can add on to our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:09:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will never die. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll live on eternally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.73,0:10:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's your religion, is it?\NThat's a wonderful way of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.73,0:10:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the correct answer is,\Nas the song goes, "no one lives forever".
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.44,0:10:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could kill you by torturing you cruelly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the least I could do\Nto even come close...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.78,0:10:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to what you did to my subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.05,0:10:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But unfortunately I'm not\Nas vulgar as you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.49,0:10:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm just going to\Nwatch you die from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.86,0:10:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from your wounds,\Nyou have ten minutes at the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.37,0:10:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dedicate these few minutes\Nbefore you leave this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...to Saharov and Menshov's souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.91,0:10:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You probably wouldn't\Nbe able to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.40,0:11:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cry, you fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.91,0:11:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sergeant.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm finished on my end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.11,0:11:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't good, Captain.\NI was chilled to the bone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.02,0:11:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.38,0:11:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had you stick with me\Nthrough all this selfishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.72,0:11:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Captain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.79,0:11:41.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting too old for this.\NI'm a little exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.51,0:12:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's got a great singing voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.38,0:12:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe it's the voice\Nof a crazed, bloodthirsty murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.75,0:12:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her voice alone is that of an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.39,0:12:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this has really taken\Nan odd turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.60,0:12:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can say that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.56,0:12:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bloodthirsty murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:12:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that starred in the night of terror\Nin Roanapur is now our client.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.00,0:13:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's fine by me. She's a client,\Njust the same. So, where's Revy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.04,0:13:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first she was really pissed off\Nabout that girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.04,0:13:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but right now she's outside\Nguarding the cabin...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.48,0:13:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...just in case something\Nhappens to Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a beautiful song.\NWhere did you learn it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard it on TV.\NThis song's one of my favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what? You're the first\Nperson besides my big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.87,0:13:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that I've sung it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem different from everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.18,0:13:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like you're in a different place.\NA different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.62,0:13:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'm just not used\Nto this job yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a nice person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.29,0:13:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I'm really good at figuring out\Nwho's good and who's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.10,0:14:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me. Balalaika?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.93,0:14:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- {\i1}I presume you know why I'm calling.{\i0}\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.97,0:14:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In fact I expected this call sooner.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.81,0:14:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dutch. Do you realize\Nwhat you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Of course.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.98,0:14:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're being paid extra\Nfor the additional risks involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.71,0:14:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not doing this for some\Nobligation or sympathy, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.68,0:14:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Do I look like a philanthropist to you?\N- {\i1}Just checking.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It allows me to determine\Nthe position I should be taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.39,0:14:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We both just gotta do what we gotta do.\NAm I wrong, Balalaika?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.13,0:14:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Dutch. We're swaying south.\N- {\i1}You're right, Dutch.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.16,0:14:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've already taken a number of steps.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.07,0:14:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I just noticed some guys\Nthat may have something to do with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No regrets and no grudges.\NGood luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.74,0:14:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Roger, Captain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Sergeant.\N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.44,0:14:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Get me the E File of the trouble list.\N- E?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.58,0:14:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Insurance with a good return.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- The Vietnamese Navy?\N- Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.35,0:15:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite impressive.\NThe power of Hotel Moscow...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Are we gonna fight them?\N- Don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.66,0:15:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're a torpedo boat,\Nand we're up against missile ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.83,0:15:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn frustrating, but that eliminates\Nthe Hainan Island route.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.64,0:15:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Brunei?\NWhere Mary Lee is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.54,0:15:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.\NIt'll take too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.17,0:15:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the only remaining option...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...within the range this boat will take us\Nis Elroy in Pangkal Pinang.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Horn Elroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.25,0:15:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Okay, that's where we'll go.\N- I'll contact him at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.75,0:15:36.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're out on the sea, but I'm not able\Nto see any of it. How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.53,0:15:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.93,0:15:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you never seen the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.33,0:15:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back when we were in Sicily...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.50,0:15:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and at the orphanage,\Nall we saw were gray walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.71,0:15:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born in the rocky\NCarpathian mountain range.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.98,0:15:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was always cloudy.\NA very lonely place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.11,0:16:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A particular dictator prohibited\Nhis citizens from having an abortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.79,0:16:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The purpose was to create more workers\Nfor this poor country...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.39,0:16:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but the fact was, if they were poor,\Nthey could not raise their children.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.83,0:16:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Massive numbers of abandoned children\Nwere taken in by state-run orphanages.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.43,0:16:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The children would become prime\Ncandidates for the secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.97,0:16:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The dictator was killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.74,0:16:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and what remained were the countless\Norphans who received no love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.34,0:16:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once we were handed\Nover to Sicily...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.34,0:16:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we were continually surrounded\Nby blood and darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.74,0:16:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were kicked until we\Nno longer moved...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.41,0:16:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and there were nights that\NI'd have red pee all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.18,0:16:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother and I would often ask\Nwhy God is so cruel to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.29,0:16:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know what? Both big brother and\NI realized something. Other children...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.80,0:16:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...would be brought before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.37,0:16:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then as they cried, they'd be beaten\Nwith bats. You know what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The grown ups were laughing.\NBig brother and I also laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.91,0:17:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought as we laughed,\Nthat it was all fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.85,0:17:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. If the world keeps turning because\Nof the people that are killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.25,0:17:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then our purpose in this world\Nis just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.86,0:17:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People kill, get killed,\Nand kill again...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.23,0:17:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and this creates a ring in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.00,0:17:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you sad that your big brother\Ngot killed because of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.17,0:17:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here.\NI'm always with big sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.01,0:17:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because we will live eternally,\Nabove this ring that continues forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.68,0:17:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will continue killing,\Nand the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.82,0:17:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the people and the two of us will\Nalways exist so we can kill. That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.09,0:17:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we're no longer sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.06,0:17:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've learned to love the smell\Nof blood, the sound of screaming...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.66,0:17:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the warmth of bowels.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.80,0:17:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.20,0:18:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're wrong. This world is really here\Nto make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.64,0:18:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Blood and darkness are only\Nvery small fragments of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's far from everything\Nthe world has to offer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.61,0:18:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Don't cry, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.29,0:18:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time I ever met such\Na kind person like you! So...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:24.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. A gift for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.87,0:18:35.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Rock?\N- Benny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.27,0:18:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go check on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.61,0:18:39.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take care of the kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.54,0:18:40.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well... I see that the blood of your\Nkind is also red. Hey, stupid brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.12,0:18:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not only the Sis'.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.55,0:18:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also really disappointed that\Nyou're not already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.66,0:18:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know,\Nyou have the same smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.93,0:19:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The smell of blood and rotten sewers.\NYou and I are the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.70,0:19:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't care less\Nabout any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.50,0:19:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You try teasing him one more time,\Nand I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.20,0:19:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, if you say\Nanything to piss me off, I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! Why? Why did all this\Nhave to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone ganged up on her\Nand turned her into a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.85,0:19:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man-eating tiger! Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.85,0:19:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock. You can't look\Ndirectly at these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.46,0:19:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is that sort of place,\Nand it would be best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I'll... I'll...\N- What? Adopt her? Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.20,0:19:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kid can never stop killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.94,0:19:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only someone was just\Na little kinder to them...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.04,0:19:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...they might've gone to school,\Nmade friends, and lived happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.38,0:19:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that didn't happen, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.68,0:19:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this story ends here, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.03,0:20:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dutch. Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.37,0:20:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.63,0:20:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- So that's your cargo this time?\N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.37,0:20:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to rush you, but were you\Nable to get her a passport?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.67,0:20:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gathered everything she'll need,\Nas always.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.85,0:20:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you again, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope to meet\Nyou again someday!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.82,0:20:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, we'll put together a\Nlunch basket. Just the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.12,0:20:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.39,0:20:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds wonderful.\NThat really would be wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.67,0:20:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How beautiful. The sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.91,0:20:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hotel Moscow, Dutch. Who else?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.41,0:20:57.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know you just trashed\Nyour career as a getaway man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.05,0:21:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm done.\NI have a son in South Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.25,0:21:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a letter from his wife. He's only 34\Nbut has been diagnosed with cancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I've grown tired of walking\Nthe tightrope. This is my last job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.20,0:21:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotel Moscow is paying me\Na pretty attractive amount for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.57,0:21:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, see ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her last words were, "How beautiful.\NThe sky." That's so unfitting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.48,0:21:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rock! Bring a canvas.\NWe'd better cover the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That won't be necessary. Dutch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.02,0:21:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is fine.\NJust as she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.16,0:21:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can look up at the sky and gaze\Nat the ocean as she sleeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.82,0:21:39.99,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits A,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Someday I want to run away...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.39,0:21:46.39,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits A,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,1000)}...to the world of midnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.76,0:21:53.79,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Where the darkness fill the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.54,0:22:00.00,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Where it's icy cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.71,0:22:08.55,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Where nobody has a name...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.79,0:22:15.09,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Where {\fsp5}l{\fsp1}iving is not a game...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.59,0:22:22.02,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}There, I'll hide my broken heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.47,0:22:28.63,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Dying to survive...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.41,0:22:35.67,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}There, no one can see me cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.05,0:22:43.01,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}The tears of my lonely soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.52,0:22:52.76,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}I'll {\fsp5}f{\fsp1}ind peace of mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.06,0:23:02.97,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}{\fsp-5}I{\fsp1}n the dark and cold wo{\fsp5}r{\fsp1}ld of midnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.21,0:23:07.94,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,700)}Midnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.05,0:23:16.71,Black Lagoon E15 ED Credits B,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(500,1500)}Midnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.56,0:23:18.56,Black Lagoon Next Episode,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur10\pos(980,916)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.56,0:23:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I accepted this job...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.66,0:23:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is because I was told I'd be able to\Nmake perfect counterfeit money.
